We have recommended management to –
a. Enforce the liquidation of all travel cash advances within the reglamentary period of 30 days in accordance with COA Circular No. 96-004;
b. Require that all cash advances be reported on as soon as the purpose for which it was given has been served and that all cash advances be fully liquidated at the end of the year in accordance with the provisions of COA Circular 97-002;
c. Enforce the return of any unexpended balance to the Cashier/Collecting Officer who will issue the necessary official receipt.
d. Direct the municipal accountant to monitor the liquidation of travel cash advances by deleting the name of the official or employee from subsequent payrolls, after due notice, until such time that the travel cash advance has been fully liquidated, if the official or employee concerned fails to liquidate the cash advance.

